<br>
I knew what I wanted to give my wife for our anniversary, something meaningful, yet simple.  And so I decided on a necklace with my life's essence imbued within.  First, I had to find a necklace which would be able to hold my life's essence, and thus I remembered mention of a Sparkling Soul Necklace found within the Tower of Frozen Shadow, and so it was there that I made my first visit.  After borrowing Mudwart's master key to the tower from Littany, I entered the tower alone and worked my way to the fourth floor where I had heard stories of a dreaded mummy by the name of Amontehepna whom carried this rare neckpiece.  After slaying all inhabitants and not finding a trace of the mummy, I waited for their spirits to reform and coalesce into their material form once again.  I made my rounds once again, quickly dispatching the weak shadows and mummies.  As I came around a corner, I heard the mumbling and shuffling that was a new sound to me.  I peeked around the corner and with its back turned to me was the beast Amontehepna.  Smiling to myself, I lifted my cudgel and made quick work of the mummy, reveling in the crunching of bones as my cudgel fell repeatedly upon the beast's body.  Once the walking corpse had stopped moving, I investigated the ruins and found to my delight the Sparkling Soul Necklace which I sought.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.leagueofshadows.net/images/Amontehepna.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
<br>
Grinning to myself, I left the tower and sought out the next part of the necklace, a gem imbued with my soul.  I knew that the bonedancers of Neriak were able to infuse one's spirit within an emerald and so I sought out the new bonedancer to the League, Dekarn.  Meeting in the Nexus, I explained my request to the bonedancer and Dekarn set about preparing the ritual.  With the preparations complete, I sat on the stone floor and lost myself in meditation, whilst Dekarn began the ritual.  I awoke from my reverie, expecting to feel ... different ... but I did not and raised my eyebrow at Dekarn.  The bonedancer was holding the emerald in his hand with a puzzled look.  He was quite confused and did not know the reason, but he told me that my soul was too powerful to be encased within the emerald.  The both of us puzzled, we departed and I pondered, wondering as to the reason behind this.  Surely, I was a powerful Dread Lord, but too powerful for my essence to be held within an emerald?  And thus I sought out the council of Dekarn's master, Xon Qeuxill, as well as my old masters, Nezzka Tol and Tralon Din'a, in the Tower of the Dead.<br>
<br>
Tallonar: &quot;Fellow Lords of Neriak, I have sought out one of your students of the dead to infuse my soul within an emerald and he was unable to do so.  Why?&quot;<br>
Xon: &quot;You have grown too powerful Tallonar.  There is a limited time when my fellow bonedancers can infuse one's spirit within an emerald, and you have grown past that.&quot;<br>
Tralon: &quot;Their powers fail against the most powerful amongst us, those that have been given the title of Lord, Tallonar.&quot;<br>
Tallonar: &quot;Then take of me my title and my rank, for it is my heart's yearning to have this gift for my wife.  Strip me of my power and abilities so that I may be sacrificed!&quot;<br>
Nezzka: &quot;As you wish it, so it may be done.&quot;<br>
<br>
And they fell upon me, each blow stripping of me some of the power I once held, until at long last I was once again nothing more than a Revenant.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.leagueofshadows.net/images/Sacrifice.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
<br>
I quickly called for one of Xon's students, Tylos, of the 57th rank of bonedancing and this time the ritual was a success.  Clasping to my breast the emerald containing my essence, I thanked Tylos for his services and next sought out Faentriel V'Ghera, wielder of the Holy Water Sprinkler.  After finding out what I had done, she quickly traveled to Neriak, and after reveling in the delight of being more powerful than I, began to deliver some of my once gained power back to me.  After hours of painful resurrections, I once again held the power that was once mine.  Yet I was not as powerful as before, the Priestess Faentriel could only restore me to the 64th rank, a mere Grave Lord.  I would have to once again regain my status of Dread Lord by smiting my enemies and grinding them into the dust.  After thanking the Lady Faentriel for her patience and time, I then traveled to the forest outside and set about slaying the wolves and spiderlings for a skin and some silk from which to make a small bag to hold the necklace.  Using the skinned pelt of wolf, I fashioned the silk into a decorative thread and sewed up the small bag.  Traveling back to the bank, I asked Antian F'Lok to see my account.  Rummaging through my various bags in the bank, I found what I was seeking, the boughs of mistletoe that my wife had wrapped up with a gift of enchanted adamantite ore for me so long ago...<br>
<br>
Tallonar comes back out of his reverie at the shifting of Didi in their bed and after taking one last glance at the shimmering emerald bound within the necklace, carefully places it within the bag, wrapping it in the boughs of mistletoe and setting it on her dresser for her to find in the morning.  Smiling happily to himself he makes his way to the bed and his wife and slips in next to her, waiting for the morning to come.<br>
<br>
